32 /*
33  * All setState() functions (which take {rhoi, rho*Em} and {rhoi, Tm} as
34  * variable sets should be able to compute rho*Em given a Tm and vice versa.
35  * This test makes sure that you can go from one to the other and get the same
36  * result.
37  */
38 TEST_CASE("setState converts rho*Em to Tm and vice a versa",
39  "[thermodynamics]"
40 )
41 {
42  const int e_var_set = 0;
43  const int t_var_set = 1;
44  const int p_var_set = 2;
45 
46  MIXTURE_LOOP
47  (
48  const int ns = mix.nSpecies();
49  const int nt = mix.nEnergyEqns();
50 
51  VectorXd rhoi(ns);
52  VectorXd T1(nt);
53  VectorXd T2(nt);
54  VectorXd e1(nt);
55  VectorXd e2(nt);
56  VectorXd P_T(nt+1);
57 
58  EQUILIBRATE_LOOP
59  (
60  // Get the species densities
61  double rho = mix.density();
62  rhoi = rho * Eigen::Map<const Eigen::ArrayXd>(mix.Y(), ns);
63 
64  // Compute a randomly perturbed temperature vector T +- 500K
65  for (int i = 0; i < nt; ++i)
66  T1[i] = double(rand()) / RAND_MAX * 1000.0 - 500.0 + T;
67 
68  // Set the state with the densities and perturbed temperatures
69  mix.setState(rhoi.data(), T1.data(), t_var_set);
70 
71  // Check that explicitly set properties still match
72  mix.getTemperatures(T2.data());
73  for (int i = 0; i < nt; ++i)
74  CHECK(T1[i] == Approx(T2[i]));
75 
76  CHECK(rho == Approx(mix.density()));
77 
78  // Get the energy vector
79  mix.mixtureEnergies(e1.data());
80  e1 *= rho;
81 
82  // Set the state of the mixture based on the energies
83  mix.setState(rhoi.data(), e1.data(), e_var_set);
84 
85  // Check that implicitly set properties still match
86  mix.getTemperatures(T2.data());
87  for (int i = 0; i < nt; ++i)
88  CHECK(T2[i] == Approx(T2[i]));
89 
90  CHECK(rho == Approx(mix.density()));
91 
92  mix.mixtureEnergies(e2.data());
93  e2 *= rho;
94  for (int i = 0; i < nt; ++i)
95  CHECK(e1[i] == Approx(e2[i]));
96 
97  // Get the pressure
98  P_T[0] = mix.P();
99  for (int i = 0; i < nt; ++i)
100  P_T[1+i] = T1[i];
101 
102  // Set the state of the mixture based on the primitives
103  mix.setState(mix.Y(), P_T.data(), p_var_set);
104 
105  // Check that explicitly set properties still match
106  CHECK(P_T[0] == Approx(mix.P()));
107 
108  mix.getTemperatures(T2.data());
109  for (int i = 0; i < nt; ++i)
110  CHECK(T1[i] == Approx(T2[i]));
111 
112  // Check that implicitly set properties still match
113  CHECK(rho == Approx(mix.density()));
114 
115  mix.mixtureEnergies(e2.data());
116  e2 *= rho;
117  for (int i = 0; i < nt; ++i)
118  CHECK(e1[i] == Approx(e2[i]));
119 
120  )
121  )
122 }
